<HEAD>TO THE READER.</HEAD>
<P><HI>IN 1783,</HI> at the Cro&s;s Roads, I made known the coming in of Chri&s;t's peaceable king|dom &mdash;a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Dover al&s;o&mdash;and next in Philadel|phia, and in many places in Penn&s;ylvania and the Jer&s;eys; and al&s;o wrote a Letter and de|livered it to the Congre&s;s in Princeton College. And in <HI>1784,</HI> I &s;ent Letters <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">me Bapti&s;t A&s;|&s;ociations; and travelled through New-Eng|land, proclaiming the day of the Lord near at hand: which I did al&s;o in Nova-Scotia, and ever &s;ince, for twelve years&mdash;And now I have written upon the &s;ubject, to make it known more exten&s;ive as the day approaches more near.</P>
<CLOSER><SIGNED>I am yours in Chri&s;t Je&s;us, MOLLESTON CORREY.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
